# Profiles & externalised configuration

## `@Profile` ‚Äî different beans per environment

```java
@Bean @Profile("prod")   DataSource prodDb()     { ... }
@Bean @Profile("!prod")  DataSource embeddedDb() { ... }
```

- Activate with `spring.profiles.active` (properties ¬∑ env var ¬∑ `-D` flag)

## Config, three ways

- `@Value("${http.timeout:30}")` ‚Äî a single property (+ default)
- `Environment.getProperty(...)` ‚Äî programmatic lookup
- **`@ConfigurationProperties`** ‚Äî bind a whole prefix to a typed record

```java
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "http")
record HttpProps(String endpoint, int timeout, int retries) {}
```

## The default

- `@ConfigurationProperties` ‚Äî grouped, typed, validated at startup. `@Value` for one-offs
